ou for your consideration, hope to hear from you soon<br><br><br><br>Allocen Plectrum<br>Wood elf Bard of the 43rd concert (admission free to guildies) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/uskalding.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Skalding</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Troubador</span><br>  Posts: 278<br> <font color=#939393>(5/5/02 10:53:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdarkbrigade51915frm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.jowsey.com/kokopelli/koko-hopi.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Introducing Allocen</span><hr size=1> Allocen, <br><br>Nice to meet you.  I am Martin the guild officer of DB.  I look forward to meeting you soon.  Yes, there is a level restriction to DB.  I would like to meet you in game in the next week if at all possible, so I can get to know you.  <br><br>I am entrusted to keep the rule somewhat in order (winks at Callandre).  Usually we take close friends and family without question as this is our family.  Pyg is still a recruit to us, so let me speak to the officers so we can make a good decision.  <br><br>I am glad you noticed the raid point system.  Many hours of thought and consideration went into that system.  Callandre was a big help in making that a reality. <br><br> <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=13541 target="web">Martin Skalding</a>58 Troubradour  <BR>Dark Brigade <BR>Quellious <BR> <img src="http://www.gifanimations.com/animation3/notes/notes_037.gif" border="0"></a> </p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdarkbrigade51915frm19.showPrevMessage?topicID=26.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| 